      <lg xml:id="TolE0146">
<l>ṇaṉaveṉ puḷḷimuṉ yāvu ñāvum</l>
<l>viṉaiyō raṉaiya veṉmaṉār pulavar</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>Among those,</l>
<l>none prevents the optionaal insertion of a nasal</l>
<l>after the final member of a <foreign xml:lang="ta">toṭarmoḻi.</foreign><note place="foot">The insertion is obviously optional. Tolkāppiyaṉār's terminology is very
          careful and very precise : whenever he speaks about obligatory ' multiplication ' of
          sounds, the term is <foreign xml:lang="ta">mikutal ;</foreign> whenever he means optional insertion, he employs the term <foreign xml:lang="ta">uraḻtal</foreign> (cf. e.g. cs. 152, 157 <foreign xml:lang="ta">uraḻattoṉṟal,</foreign> 159, 160). For <foreign xml:lang="ta">toṭarmoḻi,</foreign> cf. aphorism 45 and ftn. 39. Exx. : <foreign xml:lang="ta">katirñeriñ katirññeri ; katiruṉai ~ katirnnuṉi</foreign> etc. ; <foreign xml:lang="ta">pūnuṉi ~ pūnnuṉi</foreign> etc. ; <foreign xml:lang="ta">kāymuri ~ kāymmuri,</foreign> etc.</note></l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
